          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "3. Real-Time Streaming Workflow"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Implement the streaming workflow by opening a WebSocket or HTTP/2 connection to the Kokoro endpoint. Send audio data in chunks as per the configured chunk_size. Handle incoming processed data asynchronously, ensuring minimal buffering to reduce latency. Use libraries like asyncio in Python or EventEmitter in Node.js for non-blocking operations. Monitor stream health with heartbeat messages and implement graceful shutdown procedures."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "h2",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "4. Performance Optimization and Error Handling"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "p",
        "children": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Optimize for low latency by tuning network settings, such as TCP_NODELAY and adjusting buffer sizes. Implement retry logic for transient errors, and log detailed metrics for debugging. Common issues include packet loss and codec mismatches—address these by validating audio formats and using error correction where supported. Regularly test under load to ensure scalability and reliability in production."
          }
        ]
      }
